LightFeature.Footnote: The period of exhibition of most of the lighted navigational aids of the coasts of Iceland is from July 15 to June 1 for south of 065°30'N., and from August 1 to May 15 for positions north of that latitude. The periods of exhibition of all lights are shown in the ‘‘Remarks'' column opposite the respective lights. The lights of Iceland are lighted ½ hour after sunset and extinguished ½ hour before sunrise. These lights, particularly in autumn, are liable to become obscured by dust clouds which may hang over the land while it is clear at sea.
